                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 13, 1953, the Joint Chiefs of Staff transmitted a memorandum titled
                    “Broadening the Participation of the United States in the Indochina Operation”
                    to <persName corresp="#p_WCE1">Charles E. Wilson</persName>, the Secretary of
                    Defense. The memorandum recommended against involvement by the United States in
                    combat operations, but urged that a number of measures be suggested to the
                    French with a view toward increasing the effectiveness of the forces of the
                    French Union and the Associated States of Indochina. For text, see <hi
                        rend="italic">United States–Vietnam Relations, 1945–1967</hi>, Book 9, pages
                    11–14.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
